nsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_14906633\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Mai 29, 2025</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104hzv1743437471930.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/hzv1743437471930.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/hzv1743437471930.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"hzv1743437471930\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">UX Widget Interface Version 2 introduces a new format for the data argument in the UX\n\t\tWidget Interface API functions: <code class=\"ph codeph\">processLayout()</code>,\n\t\t\t<code class=\"ph codeph\">onConnect()</code>, <code class=\"ph codeph\">dataUpdate()</code>, and\n\t\t\t<code class=\"ph codeph\">dataCleanup()</code>. This update simplifies the implementation of complex\n\t\twidgets with sub-widgets.</p>\n<p class=\"p\">The key changes in the new data argument format include:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"hzv1743437471930__ul_vyb_5lx_v2c\">\n<li class=\"li\">Different type of properties/data-internals: For example, properties such as html, style,\n\t\t\t\tclass, value, and valrep are now contained in a single-level object, prefixed\n\t\t\t\taccording to their category.</li>\n<li class=\"li\">Removal of the <code class=\"ph codeph\">'uniface:'</code> prefix: Properties previously prefixed\n\t\t\t\twith <code class=\"ph codeph\">uniface:</code> no longer include this prefix.</li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\">These changes significantly simplify the processing of data arguments in complex widgets\n\t\t\twith sub-widgets.</p>\n<p class=\"p\">For more information about the updated data argument structure, see the Widget API functions:\n\t\t\t\t<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"yaw1701439512959.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/yaw1701439512959.html\" title=\"A function that informs a widget to provide a processed initial HTML layout to be used at a run-time.\">processLayout</a>, <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"qit1701567856567.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qit1701567856567.html\" title=\"Initializes the current widget when it is connected to a Document Object Model (DOM) element.\">onConnect</a>, <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"tpd1701568145998.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/tpd1701568145998.html\" title=\"Updates a widget's state when the data object's data is changed.\">dataUpdate</a>, and <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"eux1701568186415.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/eux1701568186415.html\" title=\"Cleans up the widget when it is unbound from a data object.\">dataCleanup</a>.</p>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/rrs1743437719263.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>UX Widget Interface Version</a><p>With UX Widget Interface Version, each UX widget receives an additional setting: uxInterfaceVersion in the physical widget definition section of the web.ini file. This setting specifies the version of the UX interface used to implement the widget.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qws1743437795223.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Migration to Interface Version 2</a><p>To work with Interface Version 2, each UX widget or your custom widget must include the uxInterfaceVersion = 2 setting in the physical widget definition section of the web.ini file. Developers must ensure this setting is added when implementing a custom widget with Interface Version 2.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/vlh1743437921753.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Compatibility Utility</a><p>The Compatibility Utility enables you to make your custom widget, implemented using a previous UX Interface version, compatible with a newer UX Interface version. It is provided as a set of JavaScript modules located by default in the following directory: uniface/webapps/ux_compatibility_utils/</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/wly1743492216107.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>How to Use the Compatibility Utility</a><p>The Compatibility Utility consists of JavaScript modules located in the default installation directory: uniface/webapps/ux_compatibility_utils/. This utility ensures compatibility of the UX Widget API's data arguments with the previous interface version.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_14906633\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_14906633\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "UX Widget Interface Version 2 Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Mai 29, 2025 Summarize Uniface 10.4 UX Widget Interface Version 2 introduces a new format for the data argument in the UX Widget Interface API functions: processLayout() , onConnect() , dataUpdate() , and dataCleanup() . This update simplifies the implementation of complex widgets with sub-widgets. The key changes in the new data argument format include: Different type of properties/data-internals: For example, properties such as html, style, class, value, and valrep are now contained in a single-level object, prefixed according to their category. Removal of the 'uniface:' prefix: Properties previously prefixed with uniface: no longer include this prefix. These changes significantly simplify the processing of data arguments in complex widgets with sub-widgets. For more information about the updated data argument structure, see the Widget API functions: processLayout , onConnect , dataUpdate , and dataCleanup . Related Links UX Widget Interface Version With UX Widget Interface Version, each UX widget receives an additional setting: uxInterfaceVersion in the physical widget definition section of the web.ini file. This setting specifies the version of the UX interface used to implement the widget. Migration to Interface Version 2 To work with Interface Version 2, each UX widget or your custom widget must include the uxInterfaceVersion = 2 setting in the physical widget definition section of the web.ini file. Developers must ensure this setting is added when implementing a custom widget with Interface Version 2. Compatibility Utility The Compatibility Utility enables you to make your custom widget, implemented using a previous UX Interface version, compatible with a newer UX Interface version. It is provided as a set of JavaScript modules located by default in the following directory: uniface/webapps/ux_compatibility_utils/ How to Use the Compatibility Utility The Compatibility Utility consists of JavaScript modules located in the default installation directory: uniface/webapps/ux_compatibility_utils/. This utility ensures compatibility of the UX Widget API's data arguments with the previous interface version. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}